.TH "stmmac_set_dma_operation_mode" 9 "stmmac_set_dma_operation_mode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
stmmac_set_dma_operation_mode \- Set DMA operation mode by channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" stmmac_set_dma_operation_mode
.BI "(struct stmmac_priv *priv "  ","
.BI "u32 txmode "  ","
.BI "u32 rxmode "  ","
.BI "u32 chan "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "priv" 12
driver private structure
.IP "txmode" 12
TX operating mode
.IP "rxmode" 12
RX operating mode
.IP "chan" 12
channel index
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
it is used for configuring of the DMA operation mode in
runtime in order to program the tx/rx DMA thresholds or Store-And-Forward
mode.
